{
  "video_id": "9NZCWeBNPeE",
  "title": "The story of a parent's transition and a son's redemption | Paula Stone and Jonathan Williams",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 13310.0,
      "end_time": 17854.0,
      "text": "Paula Stone Williams: So, I was the CEO of a large, religious nonprofit,"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 17878.0,
      "end_time": 22222.0,
      "text": "spoke at some of the largest churches in America,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 22246.0,
      "end_time": 25700.0,
      "text": "was on television in 70 different markets,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 25724.0,
      "end_time": 28464.0,
      "text": "but more than anything else,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 28488.0,
      "end_time": 31154.0,
      "text": "I just wanted to be a good parent."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 31577.0,
      "end_time": 33284.0,
      "text": "I told all three of my children,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 33308.0,
      "end_time": 35237.0,
      "text": "\"When the going gets tough,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 35261.0,
      "end_time": 38351.0,
      "text": "you have to choose the road less traveled,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 38375.0,
      "end_time": 39669.0,
      "text": "the narrow path.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 39693.0,
      "end_time": 44765.0,
      "text": "I had no idea how difficult that was going to become."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 45432.0,
      "end_time": 47909.0,
      "text": "I knew from the time I was three or four years of age"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 47933.0,
      "end_time": 49517.0,
      "text": "that I was transgender."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 50395.0,
      "end_time": 54346.0,
      "text": "I knew if I came out, I would lose everything."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 54370.0,
      "end_time": 58257.0,
      "text": "But the call toward authenticity is sacred"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 58281.0,
      "end_time": 60263.0,
      "text": "and for the greater good,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 60288.0,
      "end_time": 64724.0,
      "text": "and it asks you to trust that the truth not only sets you free,"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 64748.00000000001,
      "end_time": 67607.0,
      "text": "it will set everyone free."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 68180.0,
      "end_time": 70422.0,
      "text": "I decided to stake my life on it."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 70891.0,
      "end_time": 72120.0,
      "text": "So I came out."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 72692.0,
      "end_time": 75500.0,
      "text": "Turns out, if you spend most of your life"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 75290.0,
      "end_time": 77291.0,
      "text": "working in the conservative religious world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 77315.0,
      "end_time": 81413.0,
      "text": "coming out as transgender is not all that great for your career."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 81437.0,
      "end_time": 83380.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 84800.0,
      "end_time": 85230.0,
      "text": "Who knew?"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 85254.0,
      "end_time": 86765.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 88120.0,
      "end_time": 93126.0,
      "text": "Within seven days, I lost every single one of my jobs."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 93572.0,
      "end_time": 96645.0,
      "text": "My family was supportive but struggling."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 96669.0,
      "end_time": 99194.0,
      "text": "Most of my friends and coworkers had rejected me;"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 99218.0,
      "end_time": 101370.0,
      "text": "the rest were confused."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 101473.0,
      "end_time": 105120.0,
      "text": "One friend said, \"You really messed with me.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 105503.0,
      "end_time": 108137.0,
      "text": "I said, \"Yeah, well, get in line.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 108161.0,
      "end_time": 113611.0,
      "text": "They said, \"You were my only example of an alpha male who was gentle.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 113958.0,
      "end_time": 116572.0,
      "text": "And I thought, \"Oh. You&#39;re right.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 117108.0,
      "end_time": 119372.0,
      "text": "I was an alpha male."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 119396.0,
      "end_time": 121161.0,
      "text": "And I was gentle."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 121715.0,
      "end_time": 124650.0,
      "text": "And if it was hard for him,"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 124890.0,
      "end_time": 127648.0,
      "text": "how much more difficult was it for my own son?"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 129130.0,
      "end_time": 131503.0,
      "text": "Jonathan Williams: Estrangement was not an option."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 131527.0,
      "end_time": 134566.0,
      "text": "It was Father&#39;s Day and my girls brought me craft beer"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 134591.0,
      "end_time": 137199.0,
      "text": "and a homemade jar of pickles, which, in my estimation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 137223.0,
      "end_time": 139270.0,
      "text": "is the perfect Father&#39;s Day gift."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 139510.0,
      "end_time": 140202.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 140226.0,
      "end_time": 142650.0,
      "text": "But the question remained:"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 142890.0,
      "end_time": 143574.0,
      "text": "Do I call my own father?"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 144134.0,
      "end_time": 146935.0,
      "text": "To call him, and I continue down this spiral of denial,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 146960.0,
      "end_time": 148685.0,
      "text": "pretending that my dad was still --"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 148709.0,
      "end_time": 150875.0,
      "text": "well, my dad."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 151335.0,
      "end_time": 155282.0,
      "text": "To not call was to acknowledge that everything had changed."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 155306.0,
      "end_time": 160360.0,
      "text": "It meant that I was in for years of pain and mourning and sadness,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 160384.0,
      "end_time": 163322.0,
      "text": "but ultimately, hope for reconciliation."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 164465.0,
      "end_time": 168378.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s no playbook for when one&#39;s father of 30 plus years decides to transition"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 168402.0,
      "end_time": 170470.0,
      "text": "to the female gender."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 170710.0,
      "end_time": 172266.0,
      "text": "But my dad did teach me one thing."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 172290.0,
      "end_time": 176820.0,
      "text": "He said the road to redemption always comes from choosing the narrow path."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 176906.0,
      "end_time": 178888.0,
      "text": "And so I decided not to call that day,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 178912.0,
      "end_time": 182541.0,
      "text": "and a few months later, Paula flew out and met me at a hotel in New York,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 182565.0,
      "end_time": 183942.0,
      "text": "my wife and I."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 184315.0,
      "end_time": 186630.0,
      "text": "I knocked on the door, and this woman answered."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 186654.0,
      "end_time": 188760.0,
      "text": "It definitely wasn&#39;t my dad."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 189839.0,
      "end_time": 191482.0,
      "text": "\"It&#39;s good to see you,\" she said."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 191834.0,
      "end_time": 193655.0,
      "text": "It didn&#39;t sound like my dad, either."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 194376.0,
      "end_time": 197600.0,
      "text": "We went to lunch, and the waiter came to take our order."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 197300.0,
      "end_time": 198890.0,
      "text": "He said, \"Let&#39;s start with the ladies,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 198890.0,
      "end_time": 201730.0,
      "text": "but there was only one lady at the table and it was my wife,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 201730.0,
      "end_time": 204213.0,
      "text": "and -- oh my God, there are two women at the table."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 204237.0,
      "end_time": 206243.0,
      "text": "And my dad ordered something like lettuce,"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 206267.0,
      "end_time": 208220.0,
      "text": "and I was like, I have fries on my plate."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 208244.0,
      "end_time": 210904.0,
      "text": "Did my dad like fries? I don&#39;t remember."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 211367.0,
      "end_time": 213500.0,
      "text": "I think he liked them."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 213524.0,
      "end_time": 215710.0,
      "text": "But she wasn&#39;t eating them."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 217000.0,
      "end_time": 219923.0,
      "text": "Here&#39;s this woman who knew everything about me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 219947.0,
      "end_time": 221675.0,
      "text": "and I knew nothing about her."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 222830.0,
      "end_time": 225300.0,
      "text": "I don&#39;t even remember saying goodbye."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 226721.0,
      "end_time": 228503.0,
      "text": "PSW: All I could think about that day"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 228527.0,
      "end_time": 230583.0,
      "text": "was that it was late September in New York,"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 230607.0,
      "end_time": 233370.0,
      "text": "and I was wearing white jeans."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 233394.0,
      "end_time": 234498.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 234522.0,
      "end_time": 237608.0,
      "text": "You don&#39;t wear white after Labor Day in New York."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 238675.0,
      "end_time": 240138.0,
      "text": "There was a knock at the door,"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 240162.0,
      "end_time": 243951.0,
      "text": "and all I could think about was, here I stand in my wrong jeans."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 243975.0,
      "end_time": 246394.0,
      "text": "And then I saw these big, blue eyes I love so much,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 246418.0,
      "end_time": 248988.0,
      "text": "and they were staring back at me in disbelief."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 249120.0,
      "end_time": 253116.0,
      "text": "And I thought, \"Oh, this is not going to be easy.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 253660.0,
      "end_time": 256704.0,
      "text": "When one person in a family transitions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 256728.0,
      "end_time": 260436.0,
      "text": "the entire family transitions whether they want to or not."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 261829.99999999997,
      "end_time": 263314.0,
      "text": "Now, for those on the fringes it was easy."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 263702.0,
      "end_time": 265531.0,
      "text": "The liberals said, \"Oh, wonderful!"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 265555.0,
      "end_time": 267834.0,
      "text": "She&#39;s found her truth, how delightful.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 267858.0,
      "end_time": 270944.0,
      "text": "And the conservatives said, \"That&#39;s messed up, I&#39;m out of here.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 270968.0,
      "end_time": 272940.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 272118.0,
      "end_time": 276280.0,
      "text": "But for my family, neither extreme was going to work."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 276520.0,
      "end_time": 279103.0,
      "text": "Their anger, their hurt,"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 279127.0,
      "end_time": 281826.0,
      "text": "their love and loyalty --"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 281850.0,
      "end_time": 285849.0,
      "text": "all of it had to be brought on to the road of trials."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 287333.0,
      "end_time": 288553.0,
      "text": "JW: Was it all a lie?"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 288913.0,
      "end_time": 292330.0,
      "text": "Every game of catch in the front yard, the Mets season tickets --"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 292570.0,
      "end_time": 295380.0,
      "text": "was that with my dad or was that with her?"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 296503.0,
      "end_time": 298820.0,
      "text": "I remember this one time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 298106.0,
      "end_time": 300566.0,
      "text": "my dad took me on a bike ride through Heckscher Park"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 300590.0,
      "end_time": 302251.0,
      "text": "to teach me about sex."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 302276.0,
      "end_time": 306554.0,
      "text": "He explained the parts of the body that I now know he wished weren&#39;t hers."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 308308.0,
      "end_time": 310557.0,
      "text": "Had my father ever even existed?"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 311508.0,
      "end_time": 312705.0,
      "text": "Now, grief --"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 312730.0,
      "end_time": 314137.0,
      "text": "grief is without rules."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 315332.0,
      "end_time": 317340.0,
      "text": "Grief borrows your car without asking,"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 317364.0,
      "end_time": 318520.0,
      "text": "wrecks it"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 318544.0,
      "end_time": 320288.0,
      "text": "and then doesn&#39;t apologize."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 320312.0,
      "end_time": 321628.0,
      "text": "And I was a wreck."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 322180.0,
      "end_time": 323167.0,
      "text": "This was heavy."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 323192.0,
      "end_time": 324394.0,
      "text": "I retreated into myself."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 324418.0,
      "end_time": 325674.0,
      "text": "I was angry."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 325698.0,
      "end_time": 327738.0,
      "text": "I felt betrayed."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 327762.0,
      "end_time": 329239.0,
      "text": "And I guess I should have known"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 329263.0,
      "end_time": 331645.0,
      "text": "by the fact that you encouraged me to be a Mets fan"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 331670.0,
      "end_time": 334768.0,
      "text": "that you were preparing me for life&#39;s really big disappointments."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 334792.0,
      "end_time": 335842.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 335866.0,
      "end_time": 337150.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s true."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 337678.0,
      "end_time": 339756.0,
      "text": "And yet, there were the games of catch,"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 339780.0,
      "end_time": 341371.0,
      "text": "and there were the season tickets"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 341396.0,
      "end_time": 343808.0,
      "text": "and bacon, egg and cheese sandwiches every Saturday"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 343832.0,
      "end_time": 345808.0,
      "text": "from the best bagel place on Long Island."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 345833.0,
      "end_time": 348133.0,
      "text": "My father lived this life he didn&#39;t want to live,"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 348157.0,
      "end_time": 351578.0,
      "text": "but he lived it so that I could have a dad."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 352545.0,
      "end_time": 355283.0,
      "text": "I stopped wondering if my dad had ever existed."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 355991.0,
      "end_time": 361920.0,
      "text": "He had existed -- willfully, consciously, intentionally --"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 361117.0,
      "end_time": 363360.0,
      "text": "each and every day of my growing up."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 363993.0,
      "end_time": 365417.0,
      "text": "For that, I was thankful."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 366506.0,
      "end_time": 370147.0,
      "text": "Paula&#39;s body was hers now and her transformation was complete,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 370172.0,
      "end_time": 372534.0,
      "text": "but my transformation was just beginning."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 372558.0,
      "end_time": 376694.0,
      "text": "I had another trial, another journey, another choice to heed my father&#39;s advice"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 376718.0,
      "end_time": 379449.0,
      "text": "and continue down that narrow path."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 381880.0,
      "end_time": 384442.0,
      "text": "PSW: So most days I believe there is a God."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 384466.0,
      "end_time": 386816.0,
      "text": "Tuesdays and Thursdays can be tough,"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 386840.0,
      "end_time": 389421.0,
      "text": "and any day that you&#39;re on the New Jersey Turnpike."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 389445.0,
      "end_time": 390748.0,
      "text": "I mean, really, you know?"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 390772.0,
      "end_time": 391743.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 391767.0,
      "end_time": 395409.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s hard to believe in God when your soul is in the wrong body."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 395869.0,
      "end_time": 398656.0,
      "text": "Still, somehow I ended up in ministry."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 398680.0,
      "end_time": 401344.0,
      "text": "When I lost all my jobs, it was nothing personal."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 401368.0,
      "end_time": 403948.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s what religious tribes do."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 403972.0,
      "end_time": 407358.0,
      "text": "They believe an enemy is necessary for the tribe to survive,"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 407382.0,
      "end_time": 409406.0,
      "text": "so where no enemy exists,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 409430.0,
      "end_time": 411221.0,
      "text": "they create one."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 411245.0,
      "end_time": 413522.0,
      "text": "Right now, sexual minorities are the enemy;"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 413546.0,
      "end_time": 416150.0,
      "text": "my departure was swift and sure."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 416760.0,
      "end_time": 421325.0,
      "text": "I was surprised when my son left his job teaching in West Philadelphia"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 421350.0,
      "end_time": 423280.0,
      "text": "to go into the ministry."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 423520.0,
      "end_time": 425153.0,
      "text": "I did not see that one coming."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 426145.0,
      "end_time": 427626.0,
      "text": "And now I wondered:"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 428226.0,
      "end_time": 429531.0,
      "text": "What would he do?"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 430172.0,
      "end_time": 432995.0,
      "text": "I didn&#39;t have to wait that long to find an answer."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 433392.0,
      "end_time": 436149.0,
      "text": "Six months after that first visit,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 436173.0,
      "end_time": 438533.0,
      "text": "he invited me back to New York."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 439371.0,
      "end_time": 441323.0,
      "text": "JW: The designers of the Brooklyn Bridge,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 441348.0,
      "end_time": 442954.0,
      "text": "they had their share of bad luck."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 443460.0,
      "end_time": 446890.0,
      "text": "John Roebling, he died shortly after the bridge&#39;s construction began."
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 446914.0,
      "end_time": 448303.0,
      "text": "His son Washington took over,"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 448327.0,
      "end_time": 450654.0,
      "text": "but he suffered from decompression sickness."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 450678.0,
      "end_time": 453680.0,
      "text": "His wife Emily became the surrogate executive engineer"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 453704.0,
      "end_time": 455672.0,
      "text": "who oversaw the bridge&#39;s completion."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 456227.0,
      "end_time": 457700.0,
      "text": "Father and son,"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 457724.0,
      "end_time": 459424.0,
      "text": "John and Washington,"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 459448.0,
      "end_time": 461145.0,
      "text": "done in by their work."
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 461672.0,
      "end_time": 463194.0,
      "text": "It was this sunny day in May"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 463218.0,
      "end_time": 466234.0,
      "text": "and my father and I sat in the shadow of that Brooklyn Bridge."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 467160.0,
      "end_time": 468977.0,
      "text": "Would our lives follow the Roeblings&#39; --"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 469100.0,
      "end_time": 471948.0,
      "text": "father and son, done in by our work?"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 472751.0,
      "end_time": 475181.0,
      "text": "My father thought that her friends in church"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 475206.0,
      "end_time": 477379.0,
      "text": "would carry her through her transition,"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 477403.0,
      "end_time": 479370.0,
      "text": "and they did not."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 479497.0,
      "end_time": 481337.0,
      "text": "They ditched her and they clung to me."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 481361.0,
      "end_time": 483505.0,
      "text": "I was the pastor of a new church in Brooklyn."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 483529.0,
      "end_time": 486127.0,
      "text": "This wonderful group of forward-thinking people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 486151.0,
      "end_time": 489635.0,
      "text": "and yet, we were financially tied to really conservative churches."
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 490160.0,
      "end_time": 494658.0,
      "text": "To hold space for Paula meant jeopardizing our own church&#39;s livelihood."
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 495810.0,
      "end_time": 498961.0,
      "text": "I sort of straddled the line between these warring worlds."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 498985.0,
      "end_time": 500173.0,
      "text": "So I said to my dad,"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 500197.0,
      "end_time": 502656.0,
      "text": "\"Dad, I still live and work in your old world."
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 502680.0,
      "end_time": 506300.0,
      "text": "Is it possible that you might extend an olive branch for my sake?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 507325.0,
      "end_time": 510526.0,
      "text": "And her response was impassioned."
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 512100.0,
      "end_time": 515866.0,
      "text": "You said to me, \"Do you have any idea what it feels like"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 515890.0,
      "end_time": 518730.0,
      "text": "to finally show yourself to your true friends"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 518970.0,
      "end_time": 520582.0,
      "text": "and have them completely reject you?"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 520606.0,
      "end_time": 522910.0,
      "text": "To ask you to live a lie?"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 522115.0,
      "end_time": 524760.0,
      "text": "Do you know what that feels like?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 525105.0,
      "end_time": 527423.0,
      "text": "And I didn&#39;t know what that felt like."
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 528721.0,
      "end_time": 530736.0,
      "text": "But I knew I had a decision to make."
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 531354.0,
      "end_time": 535690.0,
      "text": "It was the decision to continue down that narrow path through nights,"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 535930.0,
      "end_time": 537490.0,
      "text": "but for the first time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 537730.0,
      "end_time": 538723.0,
      "text": "I caught a glimpse of light."
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 539880.0,
      "end_time": 544474.0,
      "text": "I cannot ask my father to be anything other than her true self."
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 546259.0,
      "end_time": 549630.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 552494.0,
      "end_time": 555321.0,
      "text": "PSW: So as we sat by the river that day,"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 555345.0,
      "end_time": 560668.0,
      "text": "Jonathan talked about his pain, his suffering, his grief, his confusion."
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 561210.0,
      "end_time": 565670.0,
      "text": "He brought all of himself to that conversation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 566956.0,
      "end_time": 568842.0,
      "text": "and it tore at me"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 571346.0,
      "end_time": 574256.0,
      "text": "to be the cause of such pain."
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 576566.0,
      "end_time": 580280.0,
      "text": "But as he talked, there was something redemptive going on,"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 580304.0,
      "end_time": 583251.0,
      "text": "full of tension but possibility,"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 583275.0,
      "end_time": 586880.0,
      "text": "grounded in that narrow path."
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 587169.0,
      "end_time": 591360.0,
      "text": "He said, \"This is always going to be hard."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 591384.0,
      "end_time": 592731.0,
      "text": "It always will be."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 592755.0,
      "end_time": 593930.0,
      "text": "But Dad,"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 594739.0,
      "end_time": 596193.0,
      "text": "I love you.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 596954.0,
      "end_time": 600950.0,
      "text": "My son is the best of me and more."
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 600975.0,
      "end_time": 603514.0,
      "text": "He&#39;s bold and strong,"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 603538.0,
      "end_time": 606333.0,
      "text": "sensitive and thoughtful."
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 606781.0,
      "end_time": 608642.0,
      "text": "I guess you could say,"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 610870.0,
      "end_time": 612705.0,
      "text": "he&#39;s an alpha male who&#39;s gentle."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 614703.0,
      "end_time": 617978.0,
      "text": "JW: It was time for my daughters to meet their -- Paula."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 618300.0,
      "end_time": 619396.0,
      "text": "We went back to my apartment,"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 619420.0,
      "end_time": 622730.0,
      "text": "and my daughters were coloring at the dining room table,"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 622970.0,
      "end_time": 623781.0,
      "text": "and there was this awkward silence."
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 623806.0,
      "end_time": 627661.0,
      "text": "And finally, my youngest asked a single, confident question."
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 628241.0,
      "end_time": 631486.0,
      "text": "\"So, Grandpa, do you have a penis?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 631510.0,
      "end_time": 634162.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 634186.0,
      "end_time": 636758.0,
      "text": "And after the tension abated and the laughter subsided,"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 636782.0,
      "end_time": 639879.0,
      "text": "my girls took their grandpa back into their room"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 639903.0,
      "end_time": 641336.0,
      "text": "and showed her their new toys,"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 641360.0,
      "end_time": 643292.0,
      "text": "and they christened her with a new name."
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 643316.0,
      "end_time": 645337.0,
      "text": "They called her \"GrandPaula.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 645361.0,
      "end_time": 647864.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 649629.0,
      "end_time": 653556.0,
      "text": "PSW: So this past summer, I had all five of my granddaughters at my home,"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 653580.0,
      "end_time": 656129.0,
      "text": "there in the foothills of the Rocky Mountains."
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 656153.0,
      "end_time": 658405.0,
      "text": "We went swimming in the cool waters of the river"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 658429.0,
      "end_time": 660980.0,
      "text": "that flows through our little town."
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 660123.0,
      "end_time": 662387.0,
      "text": "And one day, one of Jonathan&#39;s girls said to me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 662411.0,
      "end_time": 665962.0,
      "text": "\"GrandPaula, can we go tubing on the river?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 666303.0,
      "end_time": 667765.0,
      "text": "And I said, \"Well, you know,"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 667789.0,
      "end_time": 670283.0,
      "text": "I&#39;d really wait until your daddy gets here for that."
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 670307.0,
      "end_time": 672650.0,
      "text": "That feels to me like that ought to be his call.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 672674.0,
      "end_time": 676680.0,
      "text": "And she said, \"Oh, but GrandPaula,"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 676704.0,
      "end_time": 679353.0,
      "text": "he&#39;ll exactly make the same decision you would."
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 679377.0,
      "end_time": 681762.0,
      "text": "He&#39;s a lot like you, you know.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 681787.0,
      "end_time": 683331.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 683355.0,
      "end_time": 687643.0,
      "text": "And I thought, yeah, he is a lot like me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 688489.0,
      "end_time": 691723.0,
      "text": "both of us determined to find the narrow path"
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 691747.0,
      "end_time": 695819.0,
      "text": "and follow it through the long, dark night,"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 695843.0,
      "end_time": 698651.0,
      "text": "all the way to the light of dawn."
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 699711.0,
      "end_time": 702215.0,
      "text": "JW: Have you ever noticed that a child who is secure,"
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 702239.0,
      "end_time": 703491.0,
      "text": "a child who knows love,"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 703515.0,
      "end_time": 705303.0,
      "text": "that child will dance?"
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 705815.0,
      "end_time": 707531.0,
      "text": "They wave their arms,"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 707555.0,
      "end_time": 710388.0,
      "text": "they kick their legs to music that only they can hear."
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 710413.0,
      "end_time": 714270.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s the music of a child who is safe and unharmed"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 714510.0,
      "end_time": 716671.0,
      "text": "and wholly loved."
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 717419.0,
      "end_time": 719678.0,
      "text": "The day after my children met their GrandPaula,"
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 719702.0,
      "end_time": 721354.0,
      "text": "she took them to go get doughnuts,"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 721378.0,
      "end_time": 723510.0,
      "text": "and I watched as they walked down the street,"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 723534.0,
      "end_time": 725221.0,
      "text": "and my girls took my father&#39;s arms,"
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 725245.0,
      "end_time": 727207.0,
      "text": "and they danced."
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 727606.0,
      "end_time": 729935.0,
      "text": "My father&#39;s arms swung wildly."
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 731120.0,
      "end_time": 734103.0,
      "text": "You bought them one too many doughnuts, because you always do --"
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 734128.0,
      "end_time": 735167.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 735191.0,
      "end_time": 737845.0,
      "text": "I watched my older daughter take a bite of her doughnut,"
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 737869.0,
      "end_time": 740270.0,
      "text": "and she unleashed two jumps and a twirl."
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 740294.0,
      "end_time": 741613.0,
      "text": "It was perfect."
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 742931.0,
      "end_time": 744345.0,
      "text": "That narrow path,"
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 744369.0,
      "end_time": 746888.0,
      "text": "it always has its share of burdens and challenges."
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 747659.0,
      "end_time": 751908.0,
      "text": "But I was certain that we were going to see this through to redemption."
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 752770.0,
      "end_time": 753920.0,
      "text": "I looked at my dad"
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 753944.0,
      "end_time": 757933.0,
      "text": "and I looked at my girls who were dancing and eating their doughnuts,"
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 757957.0,
      "end_time": 760305.0,
      "text": "and I said aloud to no one in particular,"
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 760329.0,
      "end_time": 761717.0,
      "text": "I said, \"This ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 762503.0,
      "end_time": 764506.0,
      "text": "this is how God sees my dad.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 766330.0,
      "end_time": 768159.0,
      "text": "My father was literally born again."
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 769590.0,
      "end_time": 772151.0,
      "text": "And by choosing the narrow path of redemption,"
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 772176.0,
      "end_time": 773827.0,
      "text": "I was born again with her."
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 774234.0,
      "end_time": 775384.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 775912.0,
      "end_time": 782515.0,
      "text": "(Applause and cheers)"
    }
  ]
}